## Premise
*Breaking Bad* follows [Walter White](/Walter_White_(Breaking_Bad)), a struggling, frustrated high‑school chemistry teacher from [Albuquerque, New Mexico](/Albuquerque,_New_Mexico), who becomes a drug lord in the local [methamphetamine](/Methamphetamine) trade. After receiving a diagnosis of inoperable [lung cancer](/Lung_cancer), White turns to cooking crystal meth to secure his family’s financial future. He partners with former student [Jesse Pinkman](/Jesse_Pinkman), and together they produce an extremely pure, blue‑tinged product. Adopting the alias “Heisenberg,” White navigates the perils of the criminal underworld, confronting rival gangs, the [Mexican drug cartels](/Mexican_drug_cartels), and the [Drug Enforcement Administration](/Drug_Enforcement_Administration) (DEA) led by his brother‑in‑law, [Hank Schrader](/Hank_Schrader). The narrative spans the years 2008–2010, chronicling Walt’s transformation from a meek educator into a ruthless anti‑hero.

## Cast and characters
### Main characters
- **[Bryan Cranston](/Bryan_Cranston) as [Walter White](/Walter_White_(Breaking_Bad))** – a high‑school chemistry teacher who, after being diagnosed with stage‑III lung cancer, turns to manufacturing meth. He adopts the moniker “Heisenberg” and gradually becomes a drug kingpin.  
- **[Anna Gunn](/Anna_Gunn) as [Skyler White](/Skyler_White)** – Walt’s wife, a former bookkeeper who becomes increasingly suspicious and involved in Walt’s illicit activities.  
- **[Aaron Paul](/Aaron_Paul) as [Jesse Pinkman](/Jesse_Pinkman)** – Walt’s former student and partner in the meth business; a troubled, emotionally volatile individual who struggles with guilt and addiction.  
- **[Dean Norris](/Dean_Norris) as [Hank Schrader](/Hank_Schrader)** – Skyler’s brother‑in‑law and a DEA agent who begins investigating Heisenberg, unaware of Walt’s true identity.  
- **[Betsy Brandt](/Betsy_Brandt) as [Marie Schrader](/Marie_Schrader)** – Marie is Hank’s wife, a kleptomaniac with a sharp wit who often serves as a moral compass for the family.  
- **[RJ Mitte](/RJ_Mitte) as [Walter White Jr.](/Walter_White_Jr.)** – Walt and Skyler’s son, who has cerebral palsy; his health and emotional well‑being become central concerns for Walt.  
- **[Giancarlo Esposito](/Giancarlo_Esposito) as [Gustavo “Gus” Fring](/Gus_Fring)** – a meticulous, high‑level drug distributor who operates a fast‑food front, Los Pollos Hermanos, and later becomes Walt’s rival.  
- **[Bob Odenkirk](/Bob_Odenkirk) as [Saul Goodman](/Saul_Goodman)** – a flamboyant, ethically flexible attorney who provides legal counsel to Walt and Jesse, later becoming a central figure in the spin‑off *Better Call Saul*.  
- **[Jonathan Banks](/Jonathan_Banks) as [Mike Ehrmantraut](/Mike_Ehrmantraut)** – a former police officer turned fixer and hitman for Gus, later aligning with Walt and Jesse.  
- **[Laura Fraser](/Laura_Fraser) as [Lydia Rodarte‑Quayle](/Lydia_Rodarte-Quayle)** – a high‑ranking employee at Madrigal Electromotive who becomes instrumental in Walt’s expansion of his meth operation overseas.  
- **[Jesse Plemons](/Jesse_Plemons) as [Todd Alquist](/Todd_Alquist)** – a seemingly polite and efficient employee of Vamonos Pest Control who later becomes a ruthless associate of Walt and Jesse.  

